SIMPLE: mediterranean
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediterranean
<hw>Med`i*ter*ra"ne*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mediterraneus</ets>; <ets>medius</ets> middle + <ets>terra</ets>
land. See <er>Mid</er>, and <er>Terrace</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclosed, or nearly inclosed, with land; <as>as, the
<ex>Mediterranean</ex> Sea, between Europe and Africa</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inland; remote from the ocean.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cities, as well <qex>mediterranean</qex> as maritime.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or located in the Mediterranean
Sea or on the adjacent lands; <as>as, <ex>Mediterranean</ex> trade; a
<ex>Mediterranean</ex> voyage; a <ex>Mediterranean</ex>
plant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediterranean fruit fly</ent>⟦br⟧
